The merger would create one of the world's largest communications and
entertainment empires, with annual revenues, according to press reports,
expected to exceed 20 billion dollars from cable television, comic books,
magazines movies and the Internet.
Headquartered in New York, Time Warner had total revenues of eight
billion dollars in 1995. It has approximately 11.5 million cable
subscribers in 34 states, 17 percent of all US cable televison
households.
Based in Atlanta, Turner operates both cable networks and film studios
and had revenues of 3.4 billion dollars in 1995.
